  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-based surrogate model for hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A feedforward neural network was trained on CFD-derived shear stress fields to predict the relative hemolysis index across 5 flow-speed combinations. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
